xinit
------------------------------------------
X.Org X Server initializer

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-62
  libgcc1-4.3.4-1
  libX11_6-1.3.1-1
  run
  run2
  sed
  util-linux
  xauth
  xmodmap
  xorg-server
  xrdb
  xterm

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-10
  automake1.10-1.10.2-10
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.10-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.4-1
  make-3.81-2
  pkg-config-0.23b-10
  sed-4.1.5-2
  xorg-util-macros-1.3.0-1

Canonical website:
  http://xorg.freedesktop.org/

Canonical download:
  http://xorg.freedesktop.org/releases/individual/app/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack xinit-1.1.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./xinit-1.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/xinit-1.1.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/xinit-1.1.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc
  /etc/postinstall/xinit.sh
  /etc/preremove/xinit.sh
  /usr/bin/startx
  /usr/bin/startxdmcp.bat
  /usr/bin/startxwin.bat
  /usr/bin/startxwin.sh
  /usr/bin/xinit.exe
  /usr/share/doc/xinit/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/xinit/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/xinit/README
  /usr/share/man/man1/startx.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/xinit.1.gz

------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 1.1.1-6 -----
Bugfix for startxwin.bat:
* Really wait for XWin to be ready to accept connections before proceeding.

----- version 1.1.1-5 -----
Bugfixes for startxwin.{bat,sh}:
* Launch XWin from within a bash login shell, so programs launched by
  the XWin tray menu are within a regular environment.
* Wait for XWin to be ready to accept connections before launching xterm.
* Delete only the socket for the display which we are launching, to avoid
  clobbering other XWin instances running in other DISPLAYs.

----- version 1.1.1-4 -----
Added patches:
* Don't add '.' to $PATH.
* startxwin.bat should set CYGWIN_ROOT correctly now, regardless of
  where Cygwin is installed.  It can be overriden by setting it in
  the environment as a DOS path to the top of the Cygwin installation.
* Updated comments in startxwin.{bat,sh}.

----- version 1.1.1-3 -----
Initial release for Cygwin 1.7.
startxdmcp.bat script now accepts a hostname argument (bug 10176).
Fix Start Menu shortcut where Cygwin is not installed in C: (bug 10292).

----- version 1.1.1-2 -----
Patch for $HOME containing spaces.

----- version 1.1.1-1 -----
Version bump.
Forced unsetting of XAPPRESDIR and friends in startup scripts.
Windows shortcut uses run(1).

----- version 1.1.0-3 -----
Added postinstall/preremove scripts to create/remove a Start Menu 
shortcut for XWin.

----- version 1.1.0-2 -----
Added startxdmcp.bat and startxwin.{bat,sh} from X-startup-scripts.
Moved xinitrc dir to /etc/X11/xinit.

----- version 1.1.0-1 -----
Version bump.

----- version 1.0.7-1 -----
Version bump.

----- version 1.0.4-1 -----
Version bump for X11R7.3.

----- version 1.0.2-1 -----
Version bump.

----- version 1.0.1-1 -----
Initial Cygwin release of modular X11R7.0.


Cygwin port maintained by:
http://x.cygwin.com/
